				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">IMO, if we are to be the pet class, pets should be avalible to all mages.  But, the power of the pet should vary greatly from a common mage to a upper level raiding mage.  Just like the gear of a sk varries greatly from a common sk, to a fully time equiped sk.  
<br />

<br />
MS4 should be a spell all mages should be able to get, but it should be alot more powerful in the hands of a time mage than a normal mage.  Maybe make it so with the time focus + the ms4 pet is focused into the pet that was avalible in beta.
<br />

<br />
i feel all our pets should be like this.  with different focus items the pets grow in power and also change procs.  make the proc go up 50dd every focus effect.  make earth pet cast snare instead of root with a focus effect on it.  increase the water pets backstab, etc.  
<br />

<br />
this would give a sence of scale to pets that goes above and beyond a little % incrase in mitigation.  It would show a noticable difference between a highend raid mage, and a standard mage, without taking away anything from a standard mage.  They would still get all. the pets, but just like with 1hs dps, the pets power would increase as the better focus gear is added to the mage.
<br />

<br />
And i am not knocking standard mages, i have spend a ton of time as both,  And i feel that quests should be put in the game to allow mages of all levels to get the focus gear, but make them harder and harder depending on the focus effect.  Or have slightly lesser versions of them without stats on them.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
