			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">It really has nothing to do with how much time you have invested playing the game.  The fact is, you can't compare a bazaar geared melee to a poTime geared melee and expect them to be the same.  The PoTime equipped melee will always do multiple times better at DPS, tanking, etc.  If you assume that a PoTime geared mage should have the same pet that a bazaar geared mage does, then you are making the same comparision.
<br />

<br />
I am also not a hardcore raider, though I put in a good amount of time.  Luckily I belong to a very friendly guild where I can raid when I want to or just putz around tradeskilling or exping if I don't feel like it or don't have the time.  However, I don't expect to be on the same level as a person who puts xxx hours in each week going though constant raid grinds.  I also don't expect that in concerns to the mage class, where a pet is a large asset to the class, that the pet should remain on the same level of power as the common bazaar mage should I be constantly exping in zones that the common mage doesn't even have access to, nor having a pet die in a round of melee or a couple AoE's that the bazaar mage will not have to deal with.
<br />

<br />
The base pet should recieve substantial upgrades, we all know this.  However, the power of the pet focuses for mages should be upgraded to show what kind of increase in power there is between a 2khp 3800mana mage to a 5khp+ 6kmana+ mage.  The upgrades need to make the difference of power clear, rather than simply adding a couple DPS and possibly another mob bash of surviveability.   Pet power should be directly affected by the mage's stats so that the proper balance of power is related to the mage's own accomplishments.
<br />

<br />
Elder Longfanz Beaztmaster Feral Lord</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
