			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">/fume
<br />

<br />
If I see another poster claiming that mages (pure casters remember) should scale like melee classes do, I think I'm going /enrage.
<br />

<br />
Our power curve should be "identical" to that of a Necro, Enc, Druid, Wiz etc. If you take the abilities of a typical 65 Bazaar Nec/Enc/Dru/Wiz and compare them to those of a typical 65 Time Raider with the same core AAs, we should see the *SAME* % increase. No more, no less. We do in fact have that scaling now, however the issue is that the power curve for all of us starts too weak. The *base* pets and class need upgrading, not just Time folks. 
<br />

<br />
/fume off
<br />

<br />
Now certain lucky raiders from all class-sets will be *significantly* more powerful than their bazaar counterparts based on raid-level drops, but they will be in the minority. That is as it should be.
<br />

<br />
I think what we are seeing is the raid mages trying solve the age-old caster vs. melee equipment envy problem. I remember than back when lvl 50 was the max. Certain whiney uber-casters didn't like the fact that casual players could match them in most respects because our power comes from spells which are easily attainable by all. The return of this attitude is starting to disgust me. If you ubers want equipment-based scaling, go roll a War/Pal/Sk etc. 
<br />

<br />
/growl.
<br />

<br />
Aqui<br />_________________<br />Aquilistor Apotropacus
<br />
58 Magician
<br />
Forsaken Conclave
<br />
Bertoxxulous
<br />

