				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">/sigh
<br />

<br />
Get ready folks, this is going to be a big one.
<br />

<br />
I agree the cival war of the mage class must end.  I agree that our (casual/light raid mage) gear should NEVER be on par with time geared mages but keeping us from spell upgrades besides ancient is SICK AND WRONG.
<br />

<br />
Now a casual mage shouldn't have FT 15 unless he's been playing since beta but a time mage should have FT 15 with their sick mana pool.  I have 3567 mana and that does the job usually.  I admit I would like to be time geared but a few things hold me back.  1) I love my current guild too much, 2) I don't have the time to raid from 7pm-3am EST 5 nights a week and from 5-3 on weekends, 3) every time guild on A Ro I can find the app for has mages off their want list for now, 4) I don't really like raiding anyway, 5) Oh yeah I'm not 65
<br />

<br />
And how many time raiders can say they really enjoy raiding that hard?  Yes they gear would be nice but selling my soul to the uber guilds vs being able to do as I please while on loses every time.
<br />

<br />
Now I don't have any real problem with hardcore raiders, raid, whoop some @ss, take some names just don't try and make me feel lesser for not having a full set of time gear.  Soloers, have fun, it isn't my bag so I don't know the problems you guys have.  People like me just don't want to be cheated out of spells by making them something only the hardest of the hardcore can get.
<br />

<br />
If I struck a nerve, sorry.  But we have to come together so all of our issues can be covered.  The sooner we stop bashing our uber geared comrades and the sooner they stop looking down at us the sooner our issues are fixed.
<br />

<br />
I told you it was going to be a long one.  Please excuse me, I have an Innoruuk kill to be the mod rod b!tch on.<br />_________________<br />When all else fails, gate.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
