			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Raid players and bazaar players are using the same terms to talk about two different things.
<br />

<br />
There are really two different things meant by the term balance. The first is Power versus other players (Grouping) the second is Power vs Environment (Solo).
<br />

<br />
Mages without raid gear when compared to their peers are fairly balanced arguably over powered in the first sense even though they are underpowered in the second sense.  Raid mages are underpowered in both senses that is why many raid mages seem to be saying that they need upgrades more.
<br />

<br />
Now let me clarify what I mean when I say that bazaar mages are fairly balanced in terms of group lest there be a misunderstanding.  In a group a mage performs its class role, DPS, as well or better than any other dps class ergo the class is balanced in terms of grouping.  In addition a bazzaar mage provides an offtank that when geared and buffered is comparable to a bazaar melee.  
<br />

<br />
This does not mean said mage can solo  the same content other bazaar players can.  That is a function of a power versus environment.  Nor does it mean that the mage class is very desireable to have in group only that they as desireable than any other dps class.  The problem with class balance is that in a perfect situation no class would be highly desired in groups because they would all be equally desired.
<br />

<br />
Which is the larger issue?  Well that would depend on who you ask.  It is however important to note that the perception of a class is largely based on how they perform at the high end.  For example, if you were to ask someone who did more damage rogues or mages the majority of people would say rogues.  However, I parsed extensively during POP and can safely say a pre-elemental mage outdamages a preelemental rogue in the majority of situations.  
<br />

<br />
Raid mages need pets to scale with gear so that the imbalance of player versus player is resolved because quite simply we are no longer competitive dps in the majority of situations.  In addition, we need some type of change that will allow us more power in a solo situation.  Personally, I think the a tweaked version of the MS4 pet would be ideal.  I don't think the present version of MS4 addresses a raid mage's problems.  I think those problems could be more directly addressed by modifications to the fire pet.  Besides which the idea of a raid pet that has a confusing model and exceptional push due to the stun is just absurd.
<br />

<br />
I think the community came together and asked for a viable solo pet, which I believe was the original rational behind MS4 I think we could get it.  If we have a viable solo pet and comparable scaling through pet foci then I think both factions of mages would be satisfied.<br />_________________<br />Traigos Ode
<br />
Arch Convoker
<br />
< Afterlife >
<br />
Proud Member of Team Odus
<br />

<br />
